#ad. I bet you’re wondering asking exactly what I did… what is this? What does this mean? I am not chewed gum? Well, in abstinence-only programs, students are sometimes told to chew a piece of gum and then offer it to someone else in the class. When asked if anyone took the used gum, the teacher is told to compare the used gum to what happens once a person has had sex. In other words, they are comparing young adults who have sex to used/chewed piece of gum that nobody wants. 
I wanted to join this campaign with #TrojanCondoms and #AdvocatesForYouth because I believe in the message behind it and I think it’s something that is hard to talk about as a teenager / young adult. It’s so much better to be informed about sex and be prepared. Information is the best protection! Be safe out there ladies and gents! @TheBestProtection #NotChewedGum #InformationIsTheBestProtection @advocatesforyouth #SexEd

I’ve been pretty inactive on social media lately and it’s because I’ve been preparing to launch @team.playback with my brother @michaelcobuzio. I think this has been a long time coming, but we’re finally together living in Los Angeles and I’m so stoked to build this brand. If you’re interested, give @team.playback a follow please!

Also a massive shout to Michael, who edited and shot most of this video - his talent as a cinematographer and editor has far surpassed any and all expectations coming out of college. I’m thrilled about our team and taking a leap on this journey we’re embarking on together. 
This is a big ‘next step’ and ‘new beginning’ for me mentally and for my career. But don’t worry, I’ll still be posting plenty on YouTube :) 😎🤙🏼

South Africa was absolutely stunning. Even though it was a short trip, it’s one I’ll remember for the rest of my life. The wildlife is breathtaking. Most of the animals are ones you can find in your local zoo but seeing these creatures up close in their natural environment is surreal. I’m blessed to have had this experience with my family and can’t wait to go back.
